title: Don't Dare buy It
body: I lost my Rs. 200 on this product. All the pens are in okay condition and they reached me all 20 on time. But the quality of the pens is terrible. The ink is so light I can barely see it on the page. The pen design is worst, only after minutes of holding it my fingers start paining. Finally I had to remove the refill and transfer it to another pen case to use it. But I was so utterly disappointed. The refill writes even worse than a Rs. 2 refill and here they are selling such primitive refills with scanty ink flow in such horribly designed pen cases. Absolutely shit product. No wonder I never saw this pen in any stationery shop. The product is worse, I literally had to throw away the entire box of 20 refills in trash because they are not usable. I experienced a lot of inconvenience in using them. And I spent RS. 10 on each pen. This pen isn't even worthy of Rs. 5. I feel so cheated. Such a disappointed purchase. So if you want to save you time and money please avoid this product altogether cause once purchased you can't even return it, only replace option is available.  Horrible Experience!

body: The Cello Aspro Mavro Ball Pen is an excellent writing instrument that delivers on both style and functionality. The pen's sleek black design is both professional and sophisticated, making it perfect for use in the office or at home.  The ballpoint writes smoothly and effortlessly, leaving clean and clear lines on paper. The pen's grip is comfortable to hold, making writing for extended periods a breeze. The ink is quick-drying, preventing smudging and ensuring a neat and tidy writing experience.  The Cello Aspro Mavro Ball Pen is also durable and long-lasting, providing excellent value for money. Its quality construction means it can withstand daily use without showing signs of wear and tear. Overall, the Cello Aspro Mavro Ball Pen is an excellent choice for anyone looking for a reliable and stylish writing instrument that delivers on both performance and aesthetics.
